<TITLE> Almost 3000 fire all cylinders </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 15 (bdnews24.com)This year, 2,927 educational institutions across the country secured a 100 percent pass rate in SSC and equivalent examinations. Education minister Nurul Islam Nahid revealed this information at a press conference on Saturday. He said that every single candidate of these 2,927 institutions passed the SSC exams. In 2009, the number of such institutions was 2,726, 201 less than this year, the minister said. Citing the previous statistics of institutions with full pass rates since 2005 he said, "The number of fully successful institutions has been rising gradually because of the increase in the standard of education at the institutions." The number of such institutions rose by 2390 numbers in the last five years, which was only 537 in 2005. It was 1429 in 2006, 774 in 2007 and 2272 in 2008. This year, of the 2927 schools, 150 are from Dhaka Board, 141 from Rajshahi Board, 85 from Comilla Board, 33 from Jessore Board, 31 from Chittagong Board, 32 from Barisal Board, 43 from Sylhet Board, and 46 from Dinajpur Board. bd
